Privacy Policy for Africano Bot
Last Updated: [18-November-2023]

Thank you for choosing Africano Bot! This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you interact with our Discord bot.

1. Information We Collect

To provide Africano Bot's services, we may collect the following types of information:

Server Information: Africano Bot may access and store details such as server IDs, channel IDs, and user IDs from Discord servers where the bot is added.

User Data: We may collect user-specific information like user IDs, usernames, and other necessary details for Africano Bot’s functionality.


2. How We Use Your Information

The information we collect is used for:

Bot Functionality: Ensuring Africano Bot delivers its intended features and services in Discord servers.

Performance Improvements: Analyzing usage patterns to improve the bot’s features, functionality, and user experience.


3. Data Security

We are committed to safeguarding your data and implement reasonable security measures. However, please note that no method of electronic transmission or storage is entirely secure.

4. Sharing Your Information

Your information will not be sold, traded, or shared with external parties. It is strictly used for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page, and the "Last Updated" date will be updated accordingly.

6. Contact Us

For questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please reach out to us at [idarabdo.@gmail.com].

By using Africano Bot, you acknowledge and agree to the terms described in this Privacy Policy.
